# Copy to .env.e2e (gitignored) to run AUTHENTICATED E2E tests. Unauthenticated
# suites need none of this.
#
# The reference setup uses ONE shared secret: a password shared by all of the
# app's seeded test users, so a single value unlocks every role. Adapt to your
# app's auth — if each user has its own password, or you use tokens/API keys,
# change e2e/support/roles.ts + e2e/auth.setup.ts and the vars here to match.
#
# Emails/usernames are NOT secret and live in code (e2e/support/roles.ts); each test
# picks the role it needs by name (e.g. test.use({ storageState: authFile("<role>") })).
# Nothing to edit here when a new feature is tested as a different role.

E2E_USER_PASSWORD=

# Optional: point at an already-running instance instead of booting the dev server.
# PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Optional: override the dev-server command the config boots.
# PLAYWRIGHT_START_CMD=npm run dev
